# Codex Writer Findings — TestPage Chain: testpage-260320-203824

## Findings
1. [P1] Shallow payload validation can still crash rendering — In [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L24) the API rows are only filtered by a truthy `id`, but [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L86) renders `item.name` directly. If the backend returns an object/array in `name`, React will throw at render time and break the page. FIX: normalize rows before `setItems`, requiring a primitive `id` and a string or null `name`.
2. [P1] i18n keys violate the required naming format — User-facing strings in [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L29), [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L64), [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L78), [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L82), [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L86), [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L89), and [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L92) use keys like `test_page.title` and `test_page.error`, which do not follow the project rule `page.section.element`. FIX: rename them to structured keys such as `test_page.header.title`, `test_page.feedback.error`, `test_page.list.empty`, and `test_page.actions.delete_item`, then update the translations to match.
3. [P2] Async callbacks are not fully unmount-safe — [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L17) aborts fetches on cleanup, but the promise callbacks at [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L22) and [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L27) still call `setItems`/`setLoading` with no mounted or request-token guard. If a request resolves just before unmount or after a newer request starts, stale callbacks can still win and update state. FIX: pair `AbortController` with a mounted/request-id guard and ignore late results.
4. [P3] Malformed rows are silently hidden as an empty-state success path — [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L24) drops invalid rows without surfacing any error, and [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L82) then shows `no_items`. That masks backend/data-contract problems as a legitimate empty list. FIX: treat malformed rows as an error, or at minimum show a partial-data warning instead of silently filtering everything out.
5. [P3] Delete has no confirmation or undo on mobile — [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L87) removes an item on a single tap with no confirmation step and no undo path. On a mobile-first screen that makes accidental deletion easy. FIX: add a confirm dialog, press-and-hold, or undo toast before final removal.

## Summary
Total: 5 findings (0 P0, 2 P1, 1 P2, 2 P3)
