+# Code Review Report: testpage.jsx
+
+## Summary
+Review limited to `pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx` plus `pages/TestPage/README.md` and `pages/TestPage/BUGS.md`, per task constraints. I found 5 issues: 2 P1, 1 P2, 2 P3.
+
+## High Priority (P1) — Should Fix
+1. Shallow payload validation can still crash rendering. [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L24) only filters on a truthy `id`, but [testpage.jsx](C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L86) renders `item.name` directly. If `name` is an object/array, React crashes. FIX: normalize payload rows before `setItems`.
+2. i18n keys violate the required `page.section.element` format. Keys such as `test_page.title`, `test_page.error`, `test_page.no_items`, and `test_page.delete_item` appear in user-facing UI. FIX: rename to structured keys and update translations.
+
+## Medium Priority (P2) — Recommended
+1. Async callbacks are not fully unmount-safe. `AbortController` cleanup exists, but resolved promise callbacks can still commit stale state after unmount or after a newer request starts. FIX: add a mounted/request token guard around state updates.
+
+## Low Priority (P3) — Nice to Have
+1. Malformed rows are silently hidden as an empty-state path. Invalid items are filtered out and the page can render `no_items` instead of surfacing bad payloads. FIX: surface a payload error or partial-data warning.
+2. Delete has no confirmation or undo on mobile. Single-tap deletion is fragile on touch devices. FIX: add confirmation or undo.
+
+## Statistics
+- Total issues: 5 (P0: 0, P1: 2, P2: 1, P3: 2)
+- Files analyzed: 3
+- Lines of code: ~99
+
+## Second Opinion
+`codex exec` was attempted for an independent pass, but the local CLI failed with `Отказано в доступе. (os error 5)`, so no extra review round was produced.
